import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    plt.hist(data['home_score'], alpha=0.5, label='Home Scores')
    plt.hist(data['away_score'], alpha=0.5, label='Away Scores')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores and away scores?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['score_difference'] = data['home_score'] - data['away_score']
    avg_score_difference = data.groupby('date')['score_difference'].mean()
    
    avg_score_difference.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average score difference between home and away teams?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

    plt.title('What is the distribution of score differences?', wrap=True)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['score_difference'] = abs(data['home_score'] - data['away_score'])
    avg_score_diff = data.groupby('division')['score_difference'].mean()
    avg_score_diff.plot(kind='bar')
    
    plt.title("Which division has the highest average score difference?")
    plt.xlabel("Division")
    plt.ylabel("Average Score Difference")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    home_scores = data.groupby('home_team')['home_score'].apply(list)
    away_scores = data.groupby('away_team')['away_score'].apply(list)
    
    all_scores = pd.concat([home_scores, away_scores], axis=1)
    all_scores.columns = ['home_scores', 'away_scores']
    
    all_scores.boxplot()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of scores for each team?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
